The paper deals with a graph problem and its parameterized complexity, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The problem involves finding a complete bipartite subgraph, which is a combinatorial object, indicating that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The reduction from k-clique to k-biclique suggests that it could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of Paley-type graphs and character sum theorem suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper also discusses the inapproximability of a related problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
